# EliteScore API — v1 (Extract: Users/Follow)

Base URL
--------
All endpoints are prefixed with `/v1`. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

Content Types
-------------
- Request: application/json
- Response: application/json

Response Envelope
-----------------
Schema: ApiResponse<T>  — fields: success (bool), message (string), data (T or null). :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

==================================================
# Resource Path: /v1/users
(All endpoints below come from this resource.) :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}

## POST /v1/users/follow
Summary: Follow another user by ID.
Auth: required (JWT; `userId` from request context)
Body:
{
"userId": integer   // target user ID
}
Responses:
- 200 OK — "Followed successfully"; data: null
- 400 Bad Request — "Already following this user"
- 401 Unauthorized — "User does not exist" (if requester/receiver/profile missing)
  Notes:
- Looks up requester via request attribute `userId` (String → int). :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

--------------------------------------------------
## POST /v1/users/unfollow
Summary: Unfollow a user by ID.
Auth: required
Body:
{
"userId": integer
}
Responses:
- 200 OK — "Unfollowed successfully"; data: null
- 400 Bad Request — "You are not following this user"
- 401 Unauthorized — "User does not exist"
  Notes:
- Same auth/validation pattern as follow. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}

--------------------------------------------------
## GET /v1/users/getFollowers/{userId}
Summary: List follower IDs for a given user.
Auth: none (public)
Path Params:
- userId (int) — target user
  Responses:
- 200 OK — data: number[] of follower user IDs (message: "Your followers retrieved")
  Notes:
- Returns only integer IDs, not full profiles. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}

--------------------------------------------------
## GET /v1/users/getFollowing/{userId}
Summary: List IDs the given user is following.
Auth: none (public)
Path Params:
- userId (int) — target user
  Responses:
- 200 OK — data: number[] (message: "Following retrieved") :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}

--------------------------------------------------
## GET /v1/users/get_own_followers
Summary: List your own follower IDs.
Auth: required
Responses:
- 200 OK — data: number[] (message: "Your followers retrieved")
- 401 Unauthorized — "User does not exist" (if requester missing) :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}

--------------------------------------------------
## GET /v1/users/get_own_following
Summary: List IDs you are following.
Auth: required
Responses:
- 200 OK — data: number[] (message: "Following retrieved")
- 401 Unauthorized — "User does not exist" (if requester missing) :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}

==================================================

Examples — cURL
---------------

# Follow
curl -X POST "$BASE/v1/users/follow" \
-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"userId": 42}'

# Unfollow
curl -X POST "$BASE/v1/users/unfollow" \
-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"userId": 42}'

# Public: followers of a user
curl -X GET "$BASE/v1/users/getFollowers/42"

# Public: who a user follows
curl -X GET "$BASE/v1/users/getFollowing/42"

# My followers
curl -X GET "$BASE/v1/users/get_own_followers" \
-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"

# Who I follow
curl -X GET "$BASE/v1/users/get_own_following" \
-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"